{"id":"person.doyle_zimmerman","node_type":"person","display_name":"Doyle Julius Zimmerman","index_names":["Zimmerman, Doyle Julius"],"name_variants":["Doyle Jule Zimmerman"],"branches":["zimmerman"],"role":"anchor","confidence":"documented","privacy":"public_deceased","public_anchor":"person.doyle_zimmerman","display":{"cameos":[{"alt":"Doyle and Evelyn Zimmerman on their wedding day, June 1954","credit_label":"Wedding photo: Colby Free Press","credit_url":"http://www.nwkansas.com/cfpwebpages/pdf%20pages-all/cfp%20pages-pdfs%202004/cfp%20pages:06%20Jun/Week%202/Friday/fam.pdf","height":157,"src":"images/people/doyle-evelyn-wedding-1954.jpg","width":137},{"alt":"Grave marker of Doyle J. Zimmerman, Sgt US Army, Korea","credit_label":"Grave marker: Find a Grave","credit_url":"https://nb.findagrave.com/memorial/34266662/doyle-jule-zimmerman","height":360,"src":"images/people/doyle-zimmerman.jpg","width":480}],"details":"1930-2005, Selden/Colby, Kansas. Find a Grave profile names Leonard Henry Zimmerman and Cecilia Antoinette Zodrow Zimmerman as parents.{{cite:src.doyle-jule-zimmerman-find-a-grave.a6b1ff2c}} Family testimony gives the middle name as Julius; the corrected Zodrow parentage makes Julius Henry Zodrow his maternal great-uncle, not his grandfather. The Find a Grave memorial renders the name \"Jule\" and his grave marker abbreviates to \"Doyle J.\" The 14 Jun 1953 marriage date traces to Evelyn's 2023 obituary, written after both spouses had died; the other public sources showing 1953, including both Find a Grave memorials and the Legacy.com mirror, all copy that obituary text, so none is an independent witness. The couple's own 50th-anniversary announcement in the Colby Free Press of 11 Jun 2004, published while both could correct it, establishes 14 Jun 1954 at Sacred Heart Catholic Church, and its timeline, with the couple meeting in January 1954, corroborates the correction.{{cite:src.doyle-and-evelyn-zimmerman-50th-anniversary-announcement-colby-free-pr.ffe48c56}} His military grave marker records service as a sergeant in the US Army in Korea. His memorial places the burial at Beulah Cemetery, Colby, and lists brothers Leonard Francis Zimmerman, 1928-2010, and Cloyd Leo \"Zim\" Zimmerman, 1936-2009.","identity":"Zimmerman anchor; spouse of {{link:#person.evelyn_mundell|Evelyn Mundell}}.","vitals":"b. 1930 – m. 14 Jun 1954, Sacred Heart Catholic Church – d. 2005"}}
