{"id":"person.nauer.elizabeth","node_type":"person","display_name":"Elizabeth Catherine Nauer","index_names":["Nauer, Elizabeth Catherine","Zimmerman, Elizabeth (Nauer)"],"name_variants":["Elizabeth A. Nauer"],"branches":["zimmerman"],"role":"ancestor","confidence":"strong","privacy":"public_deceased","public_anchor":"person.nauer.elizabeth","display":{"details":"Born 7 Apr 1872 in Waterloo, Ontario per FamilySearch; died 25 Sep 1935 (stone: 9-25-1935); buried at Selden Cemetery as Elizabeth A. Zimmerman, same stone as Michael J. Zimmerman. The shared Selden Cemetery stone reads 4-7-1871 while the FamilySearch index gives 7 Apr 1872; the year discrepancy is case.04.{{cite:src.elizabeth-catherine-nauer-familysearch.66c2d521}}{{cite:src.selden-cemetery-ksgenweb.82a81b07}}","identity":"Doyle's paternal grandmother; Zimmerman union: {{link:#person.zimmerman.michael|Z-4·5}}.","title_override":"Elizabeth Catherine Nauer Zimmerman","vitals":"b. 7 Apr 1872, Waterloo, Ontario {{vs}} 4-7-1871 {{case:case.04}} – d. 25 Sep 1935"}}
{"id":"person.nauer.lorenz","node_type":"person","display_name":"Johann Lorenz Nauer","index_names":["Nauer, Johann Lorenz"],"name_variants":["Lorenz Nauer"],"branches":["zimmerman"],"role":"candidate","confidence":"lead","privacy":"public_deceased","public_anchor":"person.nauer.lorenz","display":{"details":"The original 1851 Canada census now places Lorenz Nauer, 49, and Thorothea Nauer, 50, both Prussia-born Roman Catholics, in one Wilmot Township household with Lorenz and Maria Wand and four younger Nauer children. Thomas is absent, and the census does not state relationships. This validates the blended Nauer/Wand household but does not prove Thomas as a son or stepson or settle the Meyer-versus-Wand naming conflict.{{cite:src.1851-canada-census-lorenz-nauer-household-wilmot-township.bc7cc74a}} The next useful proof is Thomas's 1856 marriage or a related Catholic baptism or burial that names his parents.","identity":"Doyle's possible Nauer Gen 5 parents.","title_override":"Possible: Johann Lorenz Nauer + Dorothea Meyer {{vs}} Mary Dorothea Wand {{case:case.04}}","vitals":"Lorenz · b. ~1803 – Dorothea · b. ~1802 – res. 1851/52, Wilmot Township – res. 1861, Carrick Township, Bruce County"}}
{"id":"person.nauer.thomas","node_type":"person","display_name":"Thomas A. Nauer","index_names":["Nauer, Thomas A."],"name_variants":["Moritz Thomas Nauer"],"branches":["zimmerman"],"role":"ancestor","confidence":"strong","privacy":"public_deceased","public_anchor":"person.nauer.thomas","display":{"cameos":[{"alt":"Photo from the Find a Grave memorial of Moritz Thomas Nauer, son of Thomas and Catherina","credit_label":"Photo on son Moritz's memorial: Find a Grave","credit_url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/48206092/moritz_thomas-nauer","height":480,"src":"images/people/moritz-nauer.jpg","width":370},{"alt":"Headstone of Catherina Nauer, 1832-1906","credit_label":"Headstone: Find a Grave","credit_url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/48214393/catherina-nauer","height":480,"src":"images/people/catherina-koeberger-nauer.jpg","width":359}],"details":"FamilySearch indexes Elizabeth's father as Thomas A. Nauer and her mother as Catherine Marie; sibling and cemetery-index evidence gives the fuller name Catherina Marie Koeberger/Koburger. Moritz Thomas Nauer's memorial gives Thomas A. Nauer, 1824-1884, and Catherina Koeberger Nauer, 1832-1906; Catherina's own memorial gives birth 4 Mar 1832 and death 1 Feb 1906. The Waterloo German Catholic Settlers PDF places Thomas and Catharine in Waterloo County in 1871 and Cawker, Mitchell County, Kansas by 1880. Son Moritz, whose memorial photo appears on this row, was born 14 Sep 1873 at Maryhill, Ontario, married Louisa Catherine Zimmerman in 1897, possibly the Louisa of John Paul Zimmerman's 1880 Norfolk household, and died 14 May 1953 at Jennings, Decatur County, Kansas.{{cite:src.moritz-thomas-nauer-find-a-grave.048597c8}}{{cite:src.the-german-catholic-settlers-of-waterloo-county-pdf.73dd582b}}","identity":"Doyle's Nauer great-grandparents.","vitals":"Thomas · b. 1824 – d. 1884 – Catherina · b. 4 Mar 1832 – d. 1 Feb 1906 – res. 1871, Waterloo County – res. 1880, Cawker, Mitchell County, Kansas"}}
