{"id":"person.zodrow.cecilia","node_type":"person","display_name":"Cecilia Antoinette Zodrow","index_names":["Zimmerman, Cecilia (Zodrow)","Zodrow, Cecilia Antoinette"],"name_variants":[],"branches":["zimmerman"],"role":"ancestor","confidence":"documented","privacy":"public_deceased","public_anchor":"person.zodrow.cecilia","display":{"details":"Corrected 2026-07-08: {{url:https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/104955721|Cecilia's memorial}} gives her Leoville birth, Colby death, Sacred Heart burial, and parents Leonard Ferdinand Zodrow and Catherine Fleckenstein Zodrow.{{cite:src.cecilia-zodrow-zimmerman-find-a-grave.5586b816}} {{url:https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/71839302|Leonard Ferdinand Zodrow's memorial}} reciprocally lists Cecilia among his children and places Leonard in the John Zodrow + Antonette Grams family.{{cite:src.leonard-ferdinand-zodrow-find-a-grave.7870a1b4}} Primary-tier negatives corroborate the cutover: no Washington certificate in Julius Henry Zodrow's household names Cecilia among the documented children, and Hattie Zodrow Schroer's 1961 obituary places brother Leonard at Selden, Kansas. The older public FamilySearch sibling-indexing basis that made Julius Henry Zodrow + Ernestina Baier her parents is superseded. The 1910 US Census (Sheridan Co, ED 0187, sheet 6A) enumerates her as \"Celia A\", age 5, a daughter in Leonard's household with siblings Leo and Mary — primary confirmation (case.21 CLOSED).","identity":"Doyle's mother in the Zodrow branch.","record_cards":["ev.ancestry.1910-zodrow"],"title_override":"Cecilia Antoinette Zodrow Zimmerman","vitals":"b. 20 Jun 1904, Leoville, Decatur County, Kansas – d. 10 Dec 1997, Colby, Kansas – bur. Sacred Heart Cemetery, Colby"}}
{"id":"person.zodrow.john","node_type":"person","display_name":"John Zodrow","index_names":["Zodrow, John"],"name_variants":["John M. Zodrow"],"branches":["zimmerman"],"role":"ancestor","confidence":"strong","privacy":"public_deceased","public_anchor":"person.zodrow.john","display":{"details":"Leonard Ferdinand Zodrow's memorial places him in the John Zodrow and Antonette Grams family; Julius Henry Zodrow's memorial and sibling memorials corroborate the same sibling group. FamilySearch indexes John as born 29 Jun 1843 in Prussia/Germany, and the Leoville Calvary Cemetery transcription gives the more specific birthplace \"Sabanka Prussia.\" Sabanka itself is not resolving in Meyers, GOV, or Nominatim. The best usable county/parish/town target remains Neu Lebehnke / Nowa Lubianka, village in Kreis Deutsch Krone, Regierungsbezirk Marienwerder, Westpreussen, with civil registry at Lebehnke and church targets at Lebehnke / Stara Lubianka. Meyers identifies Neu Lebehnke as a Dorf and points to Standesamt Lebehnke; Meyers identifies Lebehnke as having Catholic and Protestant parish churches; AGOFF's 1885 Kreis Deutsch Krone table lists Neu Lebehnke with evangelical church, Catholic church, and Standesamt all at Lebehnke. The Deutsch Krone Project shows a local Zodrow cluster; Lebehnke Catholic banns name Zodrow collateral families there; and a Polish archive catalog points to a Johann Zodrow property file in Neu Lebehnke, 1860-1873. This is still a locality hypothesis, not proof of John's birth parish yet. Antonette's memorial gives her birth as 23 May 1846 in Germany, a marriage to John in 1867, death 1 Aug 1934 at Dresden, Decatur County, Kansas, and names her mother as Rosa (Rolof) Grams, 1802-1895 - the first parent lead on the Grams side.{{cite:src.leonard-ferdinand-zodrow-find-a-grave.7870a1b4}}{{cite:src.john-zodrow-familysearch.35a4f123}}{{cite:src.antonette-grams-zodrow-find-a-grave.46e00498}}{{cite:src.leoville-calvary-cemetery-transcription-ksgenweb.6d88b722}}","identity":"Doyle's Zodrow great-grandparents; Sabanka/Lebehnke is unresolved.","title_override":"John Zodrow + Antonia/Antonette Grams","vitals":"John · b. 29 Jun 1843, Prussia/Germany {{vs}} Sabanka Prussia {{case:case.01}} – m. 1867 – Antonia · b. 23 May 1846, Germany – Antonia · d. 1 Aug 1934, Dresden, Decatur County, Kansas"}}
{"id":"person.zodrow.julius_collateral","node_type":"person","display_name":"Julius Henry Zodrow","index_names":["Zodrow, Julius Henry"],"name_variants":[],"branches":["zimmerman"],"role":"collateral","confidence":"strong","privacy":"public_deceased","public_anchor":"person.zodrow.julius_collateral","display":{"ahnen_override":"(collateral)","cameos":[{"alt":"Headstone of Julius H. Zodrow, 1869-1959","credit_label":"Headstone: Find a Grave","credit_url":"https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/111655641/julius-henry-zodrow","height":239,"src":"images/people/julius-zodrow.jpg","width":480}],"details":"Doyle's great-uncle's household - previously miscarried as Cecilia's parents; corrected 2026-07-08. Julius born June 1869 in Wisconsin per his memorial (his 1959 death certificate, State File 6169, gives 9 Jun 1870 — a one-year conflict), months after the family's reported 1868 arrival, and died 13 Mar 1959 at Medical Lake, Spokane County, Washington.{{cite:src.julius-henry-zodrow-find-a-grave.b2c95ae2}}{{cite:src.julius-zodrow-wa-death-certificate.d9291309}} The Washington certificate cluster keeps this as Julius and Ernestina's collateral household: Albert L., Leonard William, and August Henry are documented there, with Gordon appearing as August Henry's informant; no Cecilia appears in those certificates. Ernestina died in mid-May 1940 at Chewelah, Stevens County, Washington, per the state death index — which also names her father, August Biaer [i.e. Baier] — correcting the compiled “1963” previously shown here; the Holy Cross register's 11 May burial date conflicts impossibly with the index's 14 May death date, so the exact day is left open (2026-07-08 validation, Washington Digital Archives).{{cite:src.ernestine-zodrow-wa-death-index.24690954}}","identity":"Doyle's great-uncle's household; not an ancestor row.","title_override":"Julius Henry Zodrow + Ernestina Baier","vitals":"Julius · b. Jun 1869 {{vs}} 9 Jun 1870 {{case:case.01}}, Wisconsin – d. 13 Mar 1959, Medical Lake, Spokane County, Washington – Ernestina · b. 1872 – d. 14 May 1940 {{vs}} bur. 11 May 1940 {{case:case.01}}, Chewelah, Stevens County, Washington"}}
{"id":"person.zodrow.leonard_ferdinand","node_type":"person","display_name":"Leonard Ferdinand Zodrow","index_names":["Zodrow, Leonard Ferdinand"],"name_variants":[],"branches":["zimmerman"],"role":"ancestor","confidence":"strong","privacy":"public_deceased","public_anchor":"person.zodrow.leonard_ferdinand","display":{"details":"{{url:https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/71839302|Leonard Ferdinand Zodrow's memorial}} gives his Shawano birth, Colby death, Selden Cemetery burial, parents John Zodrow + Antonette Grams, spouse Catherine Fleckenstein, and children including Cecilia Antoinette Zodrow Zimmerman.{{cite:src.leonard-ferdinand-zodrow-find-a-grave.7870a1b4}} {{url:https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/104955721|Cecilia's memorial}} reciprocally names Leonard and Catherine as her parents.{{cite:src.cecilia-zodrow-zimmerman-find-a-grave.5586b816}} The Selden burial matters because it keeps the corrected Zodrow household in the same Sheridan/Thomas County corridor as Doyle's 1930 Selden birth.","identity":"Doyle's maternal grandparents through Cecilia.","vitals":"Leonard · b. 1 Nov 1874, Shawano, Shawano County, Wisconsin – d. 10 Oct 1961, Colby, Kansas – Catherine · b. 1874 – d. 1961"}}
